  <description><![CDATA[<p>Our guests just can't get enough of the Park Hotel Gran Bosco. Lots of people return year after year thanks to the family-run service, value for money and fantastic views. It's just 900 metres from the resort centre and you're welcome to use the free shuttle to town and the slopes. It runs all day from 8am to midnight. </p>
<h2>Traditional hotel</h2>
<p>The popular Hotel Gran Bosco is a firm favourite with our Inghams guests. Located in a quiet area of Sauze, you can enjoy lovely views of the resort and surrounding mountains - plus many of the rooms come with a balcony too, so you can enjoy the views and soak up some winter sun. The rooms are decorated in an Alpine style making them feel nice and cosy. </p>
<p>A good buffet breakfast will set you up for the day and you won't go hungry at dinner either, a tasty four course evening meal with a vegetable buffet is served each evening. Head to the bar after for a nightcap, or take the bus into town and discover the nightlife in <a data-udi="umb://document/a0b1d3c577424320a9af2e1af08b6887" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a0b1d3c577424320a9af2e1af08b6887}" title="Sauze d'Oulx">Sauze.</a></p>
<h2>Shuttle service</h2>
<p>Getting to the resort centre and the slopes is really convenient. The hotel has their own shuttle service running throughout the day and night, so you can be the first on the slopes each day, and enjoy a drink in town after a day of exploring the Milky Way, before heading back to the hotel for dinner. </p>]]></description>
